              <h3>Why is my dashboard MPG different from this calculator?</h3>
              <p>
                On-board computers estimate fuel use from sensors and may not be
                perfectly accurate. Measuring from actual fill-ups over several
                tanks and averaging usually gives a more reliable long-term MPG.
              </p>

              <h3>Should I use US MPG or UK MPG?</h3>
              <p>
                Use US MPG if your car’s fuel economy is quoted in US gallons
                (common in the US and many online sources). Use UK MPG if you’re
                in the UK or your car’s manual specifies imperial gallons. This
                calculator shows both so you can compare.
              </p>

              <h3>How often should I track my MPG?</h3>
              <p>
                Tracking every fill-up and looking at the average over time is
                ideal. Sudden drops in MPG can indicate issues like
                underinflated tires, dragging brakes, or engine problems.
